Eating disorders are receiving greater attention from researchers and are also being addressed via TV, film, internet, and support groups.
Columbia University is exploring whether D-cycloserine may help anorexics.
Taiwan researchers say nutrient deficiency in school children may lead to anorexia or bulimia.
A mother has written a book citing success with forced feeding.
Computer sites have sprung up which promote anorexia.
FX aired a sitcom exploring the comedic side of eating disorders, thus trivializing the issue.
A documentary film "Thin" was shown at the Sundance Film Festival.
Support groups, such as Food Addicts in Recovery, number near 300.
